The paper discusses the use of autoencoders, which are commonly used in machine learning and deep learning, and proposes a novel method for selecting relevant latent representations. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of autoencoders in image processing (cs.CV), and the learning of hidden representations (cs.AI, cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the ability to explain the learned tasks in autoencoders, which suggests a potential fit with the sub-category of Natural Language Processing (cs.CL).
